newsitem.title: UK: NWE gasoline flat to firm, U.S. sell window opens.
newsitem.headline: NWE gasoline flat to firm, U.S. sell window opens.

text.p: NWE gasoline was steady to firm on Tuesday as soaring NYMEX gasoline prised open the arbitrage window for prompt barrels, traders and brokers said.
Arbitrage bids/offers were seen only $1 to $2 apart.
Eurograde barges traded at $199 and $200.50 fob ARA and were seen $1 up by the evening. Regular gasoline was $10 lower.

A player in the U.K. bought a gasoline cargo but all other details were p+c. Eurograde cargoes were offered at $204 cif Hamburg, with few bids seen, while a bid for Eurograde, not compatible with the offer, was seen into the Thames at the same level. -- Nicholas Shaxson, London newsroom +44 171 542 8167
